edia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Tioga_Pass_August_2013_002.jpg/1280px-Tioga_Pass_August_2013_002.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8e/Tioga_Pass_August_2013_002.jpg","cap":"August 2013 002","desc":"View from Tioga Pass .","credit":"King of Hearts · CC BY-SA 3.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Tioga_Pass_August_2013_002.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Tioga_Pass_August_2013_003.jpg/1280px-Tioga_Pass_August_2013_003.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/79/Tioga_Pass_August_2013_003.jpg","cap":"August 2013 003","desc":"View from Tioga Pass .","credit":"King of Hearts · CC BY-SA 3.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Tioga_Pass_August_2013_003.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Last_Night%27s_Snow%2C_Tioga_Pass%2C_Yosemite_NP_5-20-15a_%2818127052612%29.jpg/1280px-Last_Night%27s_Snow%2C_Tioga_Pass%2C_Yosemite_NP_5-20-15a_%2818127052612%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d8/Last_Night%27s_Snow%2C_Tioga_Pass%2C_Yosemite_NP_5-20-15a_%2818127052612%29.jpg","cap":"Last Night's Snow, , Yosemite NP 5 20 15a (18127052612)","desc":"(1 in a multiple picture album) I am at Tuolumne Meadows here enjoying the fantastic sight of last night's snow before it melts away. As far as I can see the trees look as if they have been flocked for Christmas. See the next pic for a B W of this scene. That's the Tuolomne River flowing to the large meadow of the same name. Tuolumne is corruption of the Indian word 'talmalamne' which signifies 'c","credit":"inkknife_2000 (7.5 million views +) · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Last_Night%27s_Snow,_Tioga_Pass,_Yosemite_NP_5-20-15a_(18127052612).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Tioga_Pass_Peaks%2C_Yosemite_NP_5-20-15_%2818709804949%29.jpg/1280px-Tioga_Pass_Peaks%2C_Yosemite_NP_5-20-15_%2818709804949%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9d/Tioga_Pass_Peaks%2C_Yosemite_NP_5-20-15_%2818709804949%29.jpg","cap":"Peaks, Yosemite NP 5 20 15 (18709804949)","desc":"(1 in a multiple picture album) The Yosemite Valley gets the most visitors and the scenery is beyond spectacular. A smaller, and lucky, number of people climb up to the high country on Tioga Pass Road where they can find scenes like this one. On one side of the road are soaring peaks. On the other is Tuolumne Meadows, a very singular alpine meadow in all of geology. See the valley, but don't miss ","credit":"inkknife_2000 (7.5 million views +) · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Tioga_Pass_Peaks,_Yosemite_NP_5-20-15_(18709804949).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Tioga_Pass_%2829039099%29.jpeg/1280px-Tioga_Pass_%2829039099%29.jpeg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8e/Tioga_Pass_%2829039099%29.jpeg","cap":"(29039099)","desc":"500px provided description: Tioga Pass []","credit":"Modesto Enrico Rasetti · CC BY 3.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Tioga_Pass_(29039099).jpeg"}]}